    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-06-27T14:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-06-27T14:30:00-05:00" n="716"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/6–2752: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d716fn1">This telegram was repeated to Karachi and for
                        information to London and New York.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-06-27T15:30:00-04:00"
                            >June 27, 1952—3:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2947. Re Kashmir. We commend initiative of <persName corresp="#p_WAM1"
                        >Warren</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BCB1">Bowles</persName> in
                    discussing with <persName corresp="#p_NK1">Nazimuddin</persName> possible new
                        <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> proposals. <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> thoroughly agrees that momentum in this matter must be
                    maintained since it considers <persName corresp="#p_NK1">Nazimuddin</persName>’s
                    indicated attitude currently most hopeful development in recent months. We
                    suggest however that even at expense of appearing to lose some momentum in New
                    Delhi, it is essential that <persName corresp="#p_BCB1">Bowles</persName> take
                    no action on this case until steps indicated below have been fulfilled: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>If <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> Cabinet agrees to <persName
                                corresp="#p_NK1">Nazimuddin</persName>’s proposals, <persName
                                corresp="#p_WAM1">Warren</persName> shld urge <gloss
                                target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> to transmit officially offer of new
                            proposals to <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> immed.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>We will keep in touch with <persName corresp="#p_GDF1"
                                >Graham</persName> and as soon as he advises us of recipt <gloss
                                target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> proposal and their transmission by him
                            to <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> we will notify <persName
                                corresp="#p_BCB1">Bowles</persName> he shld proceed strongly support
                            proposals.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>We note in New Delhi’s 4815<note n="2" xml:id="d716fn2">Dated June 26, <ref
                            target="#pg_1263">p. 1263</ref>.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BCB1">Bowles</persName> indicates <persName
                        corresp="#p_NK1">Nazimuddin</persName> speaks of troop ratio 3 to 1 “in
                    valley.” In Karachi’s 1577<note n="3" xml:id="d716fn3">Dated June 26, <ref
                            target="#d715">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_WAM1">Warren</persName> gives no indication that ratio
                    relates to troops in valley only. We request such clarification on this as two
                    posts can render since if <persName corresp="#p_NK1">Nazimuddin</persName> is in
                    fact talking of troops ratio only in terms of troops in the valley, we wonder if
                    this may not be basis for preparing our thinking along lines of partition with
                    pleb limited to Vale only.</p>
                <p>We urgently request views of Karachi and New Delhi whether it their understanding
                        <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> wld make acceptance their proposals
                    precondition <pb facs="0216" n="1266" xml:id="pg_1266"/> for mtg of two <gloss
                        target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss>s or whether <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss>
                    intends proposals as basis of discussion at 2 <gloss target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss>s
                    mtg.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> has been advised of info in two
                        <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss>s and has been alerted possible new
                    communication from <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
